name: Startnt
Ref
details: Each single symbol refers to a nucleotide. The whole value refers to the Varsome system https://varsome.com which doesn't explicitly refers to any existing ontology and doesn't provide it's own coding - that means the values will be preserved as they are, without any mapping to an existing ontology.

name: Alt
details: Each single symbol refers to a nucleotide. NA - not applicable if no alternative genome is indicated. Notes are similar to "Reference genome" variable.

name: NM_transcript
details: Only the NCBI Reference Sequence https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/ is used
Doubts: There can be multiple transcripts

name: Variant
description: Variant description in relation to a genomic reference sequence
details: Both (1) ClinVar database https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/clinvar/, and (2) the variant at DNA level is used. If the variant is not included in ClinVar this will be indicated (how - not yet clear).
Doubts: The description is related to the genomic or to the protein sequence?

name: Type
Doubts: Which types of variants are allowed?

name: ProteinRefSeq
details: "Not applicable" values are coded as "p.?" (in cases of a splicing variant, there is no change in the protein sequence).
Doubts: Example? It could be the name of the protein reference sequence or the name of the variant according to the protein sequence.

name: Gene
details:
Gene names are written by the HGNC Approved Gene Symbol https://www.genenames.org/
It has API https://clinicaltables.nlm.nih.gov/apidoc/genes/v4/doc.html
